These are the work arounds I found before JLC had the H3LIS in its library:

for TGD/TGC's control board:

https://github.com/AlfredoSystems/Rotini-Hardware

//  ************ SETUP IR Sensor ********************
  // see https://forum.pjrc.com/threads/25532-ADC-library-update-now-with-support-for-Teensy-3-1 for details on the ADC library
  /*
   * IR back of the napkin... 
   * if max Bot RPM=4,000 then usec per rotation is 15,000
   * if we want 512 samples per rotation, then that means we must take a sample every 29.28 microseconds
   * at slower rotational speeds, we will overwrite the value (we could average the values taken in the same rotational window)
   * Due to the large 100K resistor, we want a lower sampling speed. The next three lines of values came from the test programs above.
   * NOTE: More bits will give us better (and farther) range detection.  Will start with 8-bits.
   *  Average: 16, Resolution: 8, Conversion speed: HIGH_SPEED, Sampling speed: VERY_LOW_SPEED. Time: 17.92 us. Value: 1.000000 ***
   ->*  Average: 16, Resolution: 8, Conversion speed: MED_SPEED, Sampling speed: LOW_MED_SPEED. Time: 29.01 us. Value: 1.000000 *<-
   -->*  Average: 16, Resolution: 10, Conversion speed: MED_SPEED, Sampling speed: MED_SPEED. Time: 29.01 us. Value: 0.997067

   */

  adc = new ADC(); // adc object
  pinMode(IR1F_SENSOR_APIN, INPUT);
  adc->adc0->setAveraging(16); // set number of averages  
  adc->adc0->setResolution(10); // set bits of resolution 
  adc->adc0->setSamplingSpeed(ADC_SAMPLING_SPEED::MED_SPEED); // set the sampling speed
  adc->adc0->setConversionSpeed(ADC_CONVERSION_SPEED::MED_SPEED); // change the conversion speed
  adc->adc0->startContinuous(IR1F_SENSOR_APIN); 
  //NOTE: We are not using an interrupt.  We will read it every 30us

  // setup ADC #2 (using second ADC module)
//  //  ************ End-of IR Sensor SETUP ********************

I have the accel on I2C, formerly at 400Hz, but I'm planning to change it back to 1000Hz.
All my SPI interfaces are used for the ESC's bidirectional dShot.
